<Base title="about" description="Maker and DIYer. Who's typing.">
  <h1>about</h1>

  <p>
    Maker, creative, DIYer — that's how I introduce myself, in that order.
    I write software, build furniture, make art, photograph the night sky,
    and run the basement servers that host most of what's on this site.
  </p>

  <p>
    The through-line isn't a medium, it's the making. A co-op dungeon
    crawler and an end-grain cutting board are the same hobby in different
    materials: figure out how the thing works, build one, sand off the rough
    edges, show a friend.
  </p>

  <p>
    This site is deliberately not a resume — it's the workshop door left
    open. If you want the code, most of it is on the project pages. If you
    want to say hi, do that.
  </p>

  <p class="dim">
    — placeholder copy: replace with the real story (how you got here, the
